deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Friday, February 16. Order within 12 hrs 39 mins
features: 【WiFi Extender Signal Booster For Home】Expand high-performance WiFi with RE615X featuring 2 external antennas to reach hard-to-cover areas and ensure best signal reception
【Dual WiFi Booster with WiFi 6 Speeds】Enjoy smoother and more reliable streaming, gaming, downloading, and more with dual-band WiFi speeds up to 1.8 Gbps (1201 Mbps on 5 GHz and 574 Mbps on 2.4 GHz)
【Connect More Devices to Your Network】Connect more devices that are out of range from your main router while eliminating poor performance and weak WiFi
【WiFi Extender with Gigabit Ethernet Port】Experience wired speed and reliability anywhere in your home by connecting your favorite device to the gigabit ethernet port
【OneMesh Compatible】Create a seamless WiFi network using compatible routers and range extenders so you never have to switch networks or lose signal

【Easy Set Up in Minutes】Easily set up and manage your WiFi in a few quick and easy steps using the TP-Link Tether app (Android, iOS). Find the optimal location for the best WiFi connection with intelligent signal indicator
【Universal Compatibility】The AX1800 range extender is compatible with all WiFi-enabled devices and routers or access points. It even supports new AX phones, laptops and other devices

【Not To increase Speed】Please note that all Wireless Extenders are designed to increase or improve WiFi coverage and not to directly increase speed. In some cases improving signal reliability can affect overall throughput

RE615X wirelessly connects to your existing router and boosts more Wi-Fi signals throughout your home, allowing you to enjoy smooth Wi-Fi 6 network experiences everywhere with great speed, capacity, and coverage.EasyMeshTMEasyMeshTM works as a whole home Wi-Fi solution between different access points, providing strong, seamless, stable, and scalable wireless connections covering your whole home stable connection. If you already have EasyMeshTM or OneMeshTM devices, you can economically expand your network with TP-Link’s EasyMeshTM router or range extender, without replacing your existing devices.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: 4 High-Performance Amplifiers, We Got you Covered Enjoy 4K streaming in whatever room you are in thanks to RE615X’s 4 high-performance amplifiers sending out strong signals to those hard-to-cover areas. Adjustable WiFi Coverage Keep your internet focused on a single room or blanket an entire floor with WiFi by picking between 3 strength levels on the Tether app.

OFDMA: More efficient data. Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiple Access helps integrate the data of different end devices for higher efficiency. Beamforming: Strong, targeted Wi-Fi. Find the direction of your phone or laptop, and accelerate your signal strength.

Built-In Access Point Mode RE615X is more than a wireless range extender. Simply plug an Ethernet cable into its Ethernet port, and easily turn your wired internet connection into a 2×2 MU-MIMO dual band wireless access point. Adaptive Path Selection Keeps your network running at top speed by automatically choosing the fastest connection path to the router.

Effortless One-Touch Setup Press the WPS button on your router and extender to expand your WiFi coverage in seconds. Control at Your Fingertips Set up and manage your WiFi through the TP-Link Tether app from your phone (Android, iOS), including TP-Link routers and range extenders.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy Setup fixed my weak signal for my Ring Camera
reviews.reviewText: My only complaint is the device did not set up with their method 1 out of 3 methods available. I don't like giving out my email to avoid spamish emails. But, it did install very simply after doing that. I would give it 5 stars if the first method worked.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good extender. Great customer service.
reviews.reviewText: I installed this extender this morning. Written instructions kind of confused me as I had to set it up via ethernet when the instructions suggested I set it up by Wi-Fi and then plug the Ethernet in. I was able to get Emilio Cruz on the phone at the customer service line, and he walked me through the process of resetting the extender and making the connection via ethernet. It’s always nice to be able to get rid of some frustration. A real person is on the other end of the line helping you out.
